# Service Management Notes

This file is a quick reference for starting, stopping, enabling, and disabling services with Ansible.

## Start And Enable A Service

```bash
ansible -i inv remote -b -m service -a "name=httpd state=started enable=yes"
```

This example starts `httpd` and enables it at boot.

## Stop And Disable A Service

```bash
ansible -i inv centos8 -b -m service -a "name=httpd state=stopped enabled=no"
```

This example stops `httpd` and prevents it from starting automatically on reboot.

## Notes

- Use `become` when the service action requires elevated privileges.
- In playbooks, combine service tasks with handlers so restarts happen only when configuration changes.
